title: 600. 10 Takeaways from Week 6
itunes:title: 600. 10 Takeaways from Week 6
description:
Daniel Jeremiah and Bucky Brooks look back at the weekend and pick ten storylines that stood out from Week 6 of the NFL season. To start off, the guys discuss the Steelers dominant win against the Browns (1:16). Next, the pair explain why the Bucs have a championship-caliber defense (3:15). Later, the duo look at how the Eagles couldn't overcome injuries in a close loss to the Ravens (22:14). To wrap up the show, DJ and Bucky analyze how the 49ers offense is best when it runs through TE George Kittle and WR Deebo Samuel (32:13). All that and more in this packed episode.
